. In the latter part of the 12th century, at the time of William the Lion, the surname was taken to Scotland, where it assimilated instances of the native Scottish surname <b>Harestane</b>.","English: variant of   Hasting   with Middle English genitival <i>-s</i>.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó hOistín</b> ‘descendant of <i>Oistín</i>’, the Gaelic form of the personal name <i>Augustine</i> (see   Austin  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Hasting","meanings":["English: from the Norman personal name <i>Hastang</i>, <i>Hastenc</i>, <i>Hasten</i> (Old Norse <i>Hásteinn</i> ‘high’ + ‘stone’). See also   Hastings  ."]},{"name":"Heston","meanings":["English: habitational name from Heston (Middlesex) or Histon (Cambridgeshire). The Middlesex placename derives from Old English <i>hǣs</i> ‘brushwood’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’, while the Cambridgeshire placename may derive from Old English <i>hyse</i> ‘shoot, tendril’, also ‘son, youth’, + <i>tūn</i>.","Irish (Mayo): variant of   Hastings  ."]}]},{"name":"Janet","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a diminutive of   Jane  , already in common use in the Middle English period. It remained in use in Scotland and in some parts of England well into the 17th century and was revived at the end of the 19th century to much more widespread use, while still retaining its popularity in Scotland. Since the 1960s, however, it has rather gone out of fashion in Britain."],"variants":[{"name":"Jannet","meanings":["Originally a diminutive of   Jane  , already in common use in the Middle English period. It remained in use in Scotland and in some parts of England well into the 17th century and was revived at the end of the 19th century to much more widespread use, while still retaining its popularity in Scotland. Since the 1960s, however, it has rather gone out of fashion in Britain."]}]},{"name":"Elspeth","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["contracted form of   Elizabeth  , also found outside Scotland."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Janet Elspeth Hastings was born in 1458, in England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 daughter with William Young. She died in 1525, in Wales, at the age of 67."},"et":{"1458–1525":"1458–1525","1455–1483":"1455–1483","1475–1528":"1475–1528","1525":"1525","1458":"1458","1455":"1455","1475":"1475","1483":"1483","1528":"1528","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Wales":"Wales","Monmouthshire, England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1458–1525":"1458–1525","1455–1483":"1455–1483","1475–1528":"1475–1528","1525":"1525","1458":"1458","1455":"1455","1475":"1475","1483":"1483","1528":"1528","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Wales":"Wales","Monmouthshire, England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1458–1525":"1458–1525","1455–1483":"1455–1483","1475–1528":"1475–1528","1525":"1525","1458":"1458","1455":"1455","1475":"1475","1483":"1483","1528":"1528","Yorkshire, England":"Everwyck, Angleterre","Wales":"Galles","Monmouthshire, England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Janet Elspeth Hastings est née en 1458, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec William Young. Elle est décédée en 1525, à Galles, à l’âge de 67 ans."},"de":{"1458–1525":"1458–1525","1455–1483":"1455–1483","1475–1528":"1475–1528","1525":"1525","1458":"1458","1455":"1455","1475":"1475","1483":"1483","1528":"1528","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Wales":"Wales","Monmouthshire, England":"England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Janet Elspeth Hastings wurde 1458 in England, United Kingdom geboren. Sie hatte mit William Young mindestens 1 Tochter. Sie starb 1525 im Alter von 67 Jahren in Wales."},"ht":{"1458–1525":"1458–1525","1455–1483":"1455–1483","1475–1528":"1475–1528","1525":"1525","1458":"1458","1455":"1455","1475":"1475","1483":"1483","1528":"1528","Yorkshire, England"